@doc
Katja is a simple <a href="http://riemann.io" target="_blank">Riemann</a> client written in Erlang. The source code can be found on <a href="https://github.com/nifoc/katja" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.

<a href="https://travis-ci.org/nifoc/katja" target="_blank"><img src="https://travis-ci.org/nifoc/katja.png" /></a>
<a href="https://coveralls.io/r/nifoc/katja?branch=master" target="_blank"><img src="https://coveralls.io/repos/nifoc/katja/badge.png?branch=master" /></a>

The public API of Katja can be found in the {@link katja} module.

The default configuration looks like this:

<pre><code>[
  {katja, [
    {host, "127.0.0.1"},
    {port, 5555},
    {transport, detect},
    {pool, []},
    {defaults, []}
  ]}
].</code></pre>

<a href="https://github.com/nifoc/katja/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md" target="_blank">Changelog</a>

